8. If solved_hard_coding_challenges=true: mention recursive decomposition,
   implementation quality, data structure selection, or optimization reasoning.
9. If overall_accuracy >= 95%: recommend ADVANCED follow-on topics ONLY.
   Do NOT recommend remediation, review, or re-assessment.
10. Generate instructor-quality, evidence-based academic feedback only.
11. Each strength and weakness statement MUST cite a specific data point from
    the session (e.g., "answered all 3 hard coding challenges correctly",
    "progressed from easy MCQ to hard coding_challenge in 5 questions").

SESSION DATA:
learner=${session.learner_id}
total_questions=${session.total_questions_asked}
correct=${session.correct_answers}
accuracy=${summary.overall_accuracy}%
overall_mastery=${summary.overall_mastery}%
duration=${summary.session_duration_minutes}min
peak_consecutive_correct_streak=${peakStreak}
mastery_trajectory=${masteryTrajectory}
difficulty_progression=${diffProgression}
highest_difficulty_answered_correctly=${highestDifficultyCorrect} (${bloomFromDifficulty[highestDifficultyCorrect]})
reached_bloom_L5_L6=${reachedL56}
solved_hard_coding_challenges=${solvedHardCoding}
mcq_performance=${mcqCorrect}/${mcqQs.length} correct
coding_question_performance=${codingCorrect}/${codingQs.length} correct
difficulty_breakdown=easy:${diffCounts.easy.correct}/${diffCounts.easy.asked} medium:${diffCounts.medium.correct}/${diffCounts.medium.asked} hard:${diffCounts.hard.correct}/${diffCounts.hard.asked}
question_type_breakdown=${Object.entries(typeCounts).map(([t,v])=>`${t}:${v.correct}/${v.asked}`).join(' ')}

TOPIC PERFORMANCE:
${topicQAEvidence}

Q&A PROGRESSION:
${qaDetailedList}

${observedMisconceptions.length > 0 ? 'KAA-IDENTIFIED MISCONCEPTIONS (only for topics with errors):\n' + observedMisconceptions.join('; ') : 'NO MISCONCEPTIONS IDENTIFIED (learner performed correctly)'}

Return ONLY raw JSON. No markdown. No text before or after.

{"report_title":"Java Programming Assessment - Personalised Feedback Report","generated_at":"${new Date().toISOString()}","learner_id":"${session.learner_id}","session_id":"${session.session_id}","overall_assessment":"<2-3 sentences based STRICTLY on session data above — mastery %, Bloom level reached, coding performance>","overall_grade":"<Excellent|Good|Satisfactory|Needs Improvement|Poor>","overall_mastery_percentage":${summary.overall_mastery},"overall_accuracy_percentage":${summary.overall_accuracy},"session_duration_minutes":${summary.session_duration_minutes},"total_questions":${session.total_questions_asked},"total_correct":${session.correct_answers},"key_strengths":["<specific strength 1 observed in data>","<specific strength 2 observed in data>"],"key_weaknesses":${observedMisconceptions.length > 0 ? '["<specific weakness observed in data>"]' : '[]'},"topic_reports":[${topicDetails.map(t => `{"topic_name":"${t.topic}","mastery_percentage":${t.mastery_score},"is_mastered":${t.is_mastered},"questions_asked":${t.questions_asked},"correct_answers":${t.correct},"accuracy":${t.accuracy},"strengths":"<specific strength for ${t.topic} based on actual q/a data>","weaknesses":${t.correct < t.questions_asked ? `"<specific weakness for ${t.topic} based on actual errors>"` : '"none observed"'},"misconceptions_found":${observedMisconceptions.length > 0 && t.correct < t.questions_asked ? '["<misconception observed for this topic only if errors exist>"]' : '[]'},"improvement_plan":"<plan specific to ${t.topic} performance: mastery=${t.mastery_score}% accuracy=${t.accuracy}%>","recommended_exercises":["<exercise specific to ${t.topic}>"]}`).join(',')}],"learning_path":{"immediate_focus":"<topic with lowest mastery or next challenge if all mastered>","week_1_goals":["<specific measurable goal based on this session>"],"long_term_goals":["<advanced topic recommendation if mastery >= 90, else targeted improvement>"]},"motivational_message":"<personalized message referencing actual achievement: mastery score, Bloom level, or specific question type success>","next_assessment_recommendation":"<specific recommendation based on mastery level and progression>"}`;

